speaker: ['Monica Geller']
transcript: Guys, hurry up! The flight leaves in four hours! It could take time to get a taxi! There could be traffic! The plane could leave early! When we get to London, there could be a line at customs! Come on!!

transcript: What do you got there?

transcript: Condoms, dude!

transcript: How come the writing is in Spanish?

transcript: Don't read my condoms!

transcript: Passport, check! Camera, check! Traveller's cheques, check!

transcript: Myself. Y'know for remembering to pack a thing. Yeah, you do a good thing, you get a check! My mom does it, I never realised it was weird.

transcript: Hey!

transcript: Hey!

transcript: Hey! Are you ready yet?

transcript: Yep! You got the tickets?

transcript: Oh! Got 'em right here, check!

transcript: Yeah, in my third drawer on my dresser. You don't want to lose that.

transcript: Ohh!!

speaker: ['Chandler Bing']
transcript: There it is.

transcript: Come on! Do something!

speaker: ['Chandler Bing']
transcript: I am, I'm ignoring you.

transcript: Okay, here! I wanna be the on camera guy. All right, first stop, Westminster Abbey.

speaker: ['Chandler Bing']
transcript: Oh, what the hell is that?

transcript: It's London, baby! All right, the hotel's here. Wait. No, we wanna go... No. I know. I'm gonna have to go into the map.

transcript: Okay, if you see a little version of me in there? Kill it!

speaker: ['Joey Tribbiani']
transcript: I got it! Here we go.

speaker: ['Chandler Bing']
transcript: Okay. Listen-listen, we're not gonna have to walk this way the entire time are we?

speaker: ['Joey Tribbiani']
transcript: Shhh! Man, you made me lose it!

speaker: ['Emily Waltham']
transcript: ...and that was all before 10 o'clock. The caterer rang and said it was going to be Chicken Kiev instead of Chicken Tarragon. And then the florist phoned to say there aren't any tulips. Oh, and the chilliest has carpel-tunel syndrome. We're not gonna be...

transcript: Whoa-whoa-whoa! Emily, honey, okay?

transcript: Well, up yours too!

transcript: What?!

transcript: Oh, that's not what it means?

transcript: No! No! That's-that's time-out!

speaker: ['Emily Waltham']
transcript: Sorry.

speaker: ['Ross Geller']
transcript: Sweetie, you gotta relax. Everything's gonna be great, okay? Come on. Come on.

speaker: ['Monica Geller']
transcript: Chicken Kiev?

speaker: ['Ross Geller']
transcript: Um-hmm! Doesn't that sound delicious at the last minute?

speaker: ['Monica Geller']
transcript: Yeah, y'know, but something like salmon which would be so much more elegant than the chicken. And, you wouldn't have to worry about the salmonella. But of course with salmon you'd have to worry about the chickenella... So, I can't wait to see this place you're getting married!

speaker: ['Ross Geller']
transcript: Yeah. Yeah. Yes, this place is beautiful. Emily's parents got married here.

speaker: ['Emily Waltham']
transcript: I still can't believe they're tearing it down. It really is the most lovely building you'll ever see. I mean it's over... Oh my God!

speaker: ['Monica Geller']
transcript: It's nice.

speaker: ['Emily Waltham']
transcript: Oh. Oh.

speaker: ['Emily Waltham']
transcript: Oh. Oh my God. How can this be happening? What are we going to do?

speaker: ['Ross Geller']
transcript: It's all right! Everything's gonna be all right.

transcript: How's it gonna be all right?!

speaker: ['Ross Geller']
transcript: Uh-huh, I see that.

speaker: ['Monica Geller']
transcript: Okay, I talked to the guy with the shovel and I found out what happened.

speaker: ['Ross Geller']
transcript: What? What?

speaker: ['Monica Geller']
transcript: They tore it down a few days early.

speaker: ['Joey Tribbiani']
transcript: All right! Westminster Abbey! Hands down, best Abbey I've ever seen. Hey! Okay. What do you think of the Abbey, Chandler?

transcript: I think it's great. It's great. Y'know, they're thinking of changing the name of this place.

transcript: To Put the Camera Away!!!

transcript: Man, you are Westminster Crabby.

transcript: Don't worry. You'll find some place to get married.

speaker: ['Monica Geller']
transcript: Oowww!!

transcript: Sorry. Lucky this dress is red!

transcript: We can't find another place. Then we can't have the wedding! I've ordered chicken and salad and-and cake for 150. What should be the most wonderful day of my life is rapidly turning into just Sunday with a spectacular amount of food!

speaker: ['Monica Geller']
transcript: You're gonna find a place. But even if - God forbid - you didn't.. So you postpone the wedding. Is that really so bad? I mean, think about it. You could take all the time you needed to get everything that you want. You could have tulips, you could have salmon.... Mmmmm... Salmon!!

speaker: ['Emily Waltham']
transcript: I suppose it wouldn't be the end of the world... Oh, thank you!

transcript: But either way... You're gonna get married, you're gonna be happy, my mom's gonna like you better than me.

transcript: Oh. Oh.

transcript: Oh, honey! Don't get up! What do you need?

transcript: Oh, no. Oh, nothing.

transcript: Come on! I am here to take care of you! What do you need? Anything.

transcript: Okay, I have a wedgie.

transcript: Okay, that is all you.

transcript: So-so, what do you want for lunch?

transcript: Oh, I don't know. I guess we have to eat.

transcript: Yeah, I do. What's the matter?

transcript: I'm just bummed about the way I left things with Ross. I shouldn't have lied to him about having to work. He seemed so mad at me.

transcript: Still in love with?!

transcript: Yeah!

transcript: I'm not in love with Ross!

speaker: ['Phoebe Buffay']
transcript: Oh. No. No. Good! Yeah, me neither.

speaker: ['Rachel Green']
transcript: Phoebe, I'm going to Ross's wedding because he is my ex-boyfriend and that would be really uncomfortable. Not because, I'm still in love with him! I mean, hey, y'know, I like Ross as much as the next guy, y'know? Clearly I have feelings for him, but feelings don't mean love! I mean, I still have loving feelings for Ross. Yeah! But, I have, I have continuing feelings of love, but that doesn't mean that-that I'm still in love with him. Y'know? I-I have sexual feelings for him, but I do love him-Ohh! Oh my God! Oh my-why didn't you tell me?!!

speaker: ['Phoebe Buffay']
transcript: We thought you knew!

speaker: ['Rachel Green']
transcript: We?!

transcript: Yeah, we all know! We talk about it all the time!

transcript: You all know? Does Ross know?

transcript: Oh no, Ross doesn't know anything.

speaker: ['Rachel Green']
transcript: Oh, I can not believe you didn't tell me!

speaker: ['Phoebe Buffay']
transcript: Well, because we thought you knew!! It's so obvious! God, that would be like telling Monica, "Hey, you like things clean." Or, y'know, "Hey, Joey, you're gay."

transcript: What?!

speaker: ['Phoebe Buffay']
transcript: Oh, please! She's always got a broom in her hand!

transcript: Hey!

transcript: So, what are you guys in the market for? We've got uh, scarves, tulip post cards...

speaker: ['Joey Tribbiani']
transcript: Check this out? Huh? Yeah. That's the stuff. What do you think?

transcript: Well, I don't have to buy that, "I'm with stupid" T-shirt anymore.

transcript: Well, I like it. Here you go.

transcript: All right, look, you're not really gonna buy that are you? Don't you think you've embarrassed me enough for one day?

transcript: Oh, I embarrass you?

transcript: How can I answer that when I'm pretending I don't know you?

speaker: ['The Vendor']
transcript: He's just jealous. You'll fit right in; all Londoners wear them!

transcript: Oh really? Then how come no one here is wearing them?

speaker: ['The Vendor']
transcript: They're all tourists.

transcript: All right, look, if you insist on wearing that, in public, y'know, you're gonna spend the rest of the afternoon all by yourself.

transcript: Oh yeah? If you're gonna make me choose between you and the hat? I choose the hat.

transcript: Good choice.

transcript: Thanks.

transcript: Okay, wait. All right, that's it, okay, I'm out of here. I am not going to be embarrassed anymore!

transcript: How you doin'? Joey Tribbiani, America.

transcript: Hey! I just spoke to your dad, and you know what? He seems to think we'll be able to find a new place for the wedding.

transcript: I realise that people are going to be disappointed. But, I'm sure they'll come back when we can do it right.

transcript: I can't ask people to do that? Would you ask people to do that?

transcript: Don't you point your pants at me! We have no choice! Anywhere that's half-decent would've be booked months ago, Ross don't you understand? This is our wedding I'm talking about.

transcript: The only thing I understand is; postponing it is not an option. This is when we're getting married.

transcript: There's no 'or' in mind. What is wrong with these pants?!!

transcript: It's not the pants. It's you that is backwards. And if, and if you don't understand how important this is to me, well then, perhaps we shouldn't get married at all!

transcript: No, wait! Emily! No, wait, stop! Emily, please-

transcript: I'll get it.

transcript: Hey, Pheebs! It's Joey!

transcript: Hey, Joey! Hey! Ooh! Ooh! I just say someone on the-that looks just like you on the subway. And I was gonna go over and say 'hi!' but then I figured, he doesn't care if he looks like you.

transcript: That just cost me four bucks. But uh listen, I just called to see how the chick and the duck are doing?

transcript: All right, the seven of us miss you.

transcript: I tell you, this wedding is not going to happen.

transcript: Oh God.

transcript: Okay? But-but imagine a lot more lights, okay? And-and y'know fewer bricks, and-and-and flowers, and candles...

transcript: And the musicians, look, they can go over here , okay? And the chairs can face this way , and... You go.

transcript: But-but, if you don't love this, we'll do it in any other place at any other time. Really, it's fine, whatever you want.

transcript: It's perfect.

transcript: Yeah, it's in the guys' apartment under the sink. Why?

transcript: Because I'm going to London.

transcript: Yeah, I have to tell Ross that I love him. Now honey, you take care, you don't have those babies until I get back.
